    "z m, z ∈ [0, 1],we obtain the elementwise expansionK β = e -β ∞ m=0 β m m!",
    "K m 0,where K m 0 denotes the m-th Hadamard (entrywise) power: (K m 0) pq = (K 0) m pq.",
    "Because K 0 ⪰ 0 and has nonnegative entries, the Schur product theorem implies that each Hadamard power K m 0 is PSD.",
    "All coefficients e -β β m /m!",
    "are nonnegative, hence K β is a nonnegative linear combination of PSD matrices and is therefore PSD."
